    "english_translation": "Narrated by Ibrahim al-Taymi: My father was wearing a simple cotton shirt with sleeves reaching to his wrists. I said to him: Father, why don't you wear better clothing? He said: I came to Basra and found thousands of dinars but I was not happy about them, nor did I think to return to them. I would have wished that every delicious food I ate would go into the mouth of the person I hated most. He said: I heard Abu al-Darda saying: Verily, the owner of two dirhams will have a more severe accounting on the Day of Resurrection than the owner of one dirham.",
